safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: Caller must be approved to manage the tokens being transferred out of the `_from` account. MUST revert if `_to` is the zero address. MUST revert if length of `_typeIDs` is not the same as length of `_values`. MUST revert if any of the balance(s) of the holder(s) for token(s) in `_typeIDs` is lower than the respective amount(s) in `_values` sent to the recipient. MUST revert on any other error. MUST emit `TransferSingle` or `TransferBatch` event(s).

params._typeIDs: IDs of each token type (order and length must match _values array)
params._values: Transfer amounts per token type (order and length must match _typeIDs array)

safeFullBatchTransferFrom(address[],addr.details: Caller must be approved or be an owner of the credit being transferred. MUST be revert if the `_typeID` is invalid. MUST be revert if no authorized to transfer. MUST be revert if `_from`'s `_typeID` balance less than `_value`. MUST be revert if `_from` or `_to` is the zero address. MUST be revert if `_to` is a smart contract but does not implement EER2TokenReceiver. MUST be revert if number of `_froms` `_tos` `_typeIDs` and `_values` does not eqaul. MUST emit TransferFullBatch event.

params._typeIDs: List of ID of the credit types

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Caller must be approved to manage the tokens being transferred out of the `_from` account. MUST revert if `_to` is the zero address. MUST revert if balance of holder for token `_typeID` is lower than the `_value` sent. MUST revert on any other error. MUST emit the `TransferSingle` event.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: MUST emit the ApprovalForAll event on success.

params._approved: True if the operator is approved, false to revoke approval
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators

params._to: New minter, in case of address 0 the authorized will be locked forever
params._typeID: Credit _typeID (when credit is fungible) or _type (when credit is non-fungible)
